Change: Offline service-layer groundwork batch -- hardened offlineSyncService.ts with real test coverage, and extended the offline outbox to two not-yet-active features (stock movements, receipt-image import) per the user's "perform 1, 2 and 3" instruction after reviewing docs/future-stock-management.md and docs/future-receipt-import.md.
Implementation (1 - hardening): Expanded offlineSyncService.test.ts from 1 test to 8, adding shared `emptyPull`/`pendingRecord` fixtures and hoisted mocks for getOutboxRecord/putOutboxRecord/deleteOutboxRecord/putConflictRecord/putEncryptedEntity/deleteEncryptedEntity plus a pass-through encryptionService mock. New coverage: outbox record deleted on accepted push; conflict recorded and outbox marked "conflict" on push conflict; outbox marked "failed" and retryCount incremented on rejection; a network failure stays "pending"/retryable through the 4th attempt then becomes "failed" on the 5th; applyCloudChange writes created/updated entities to the local encrypted store and removes them on delete. All 8 passed against the existing, unmodified implementation -- confirms prior logic was already correct, this was pure test-debt payoff.
Implementation (2 - stock): Recreated mbam-web/src/types/stock.ts verbatim from git history (`git show efc3af9:...`, deleted 2026-06-18 as unreferenced dead code) with a header note on why it came back. Added new mbam-web/src/services/stock/stockLocalRepository.ts: `queueStockMovement` builds a StockMovementDraft and pushes it through the existing generic queueOfflineOperation outbox after checking the offline grant covers the business and holds a `stock.movement.create` permission (fail-closed -- no backend grants this permission yet, so the function is reachable but always throws today, matching docs/security-rules.md's "frontend checks are usability controls, not authority"); `listQueuedStockMovements` reads pending/syncing/conflict/failed outbox records filtered to entityType "stock_movement" and decrypts them (no separate mutable entity-store copy, since a stock movement is a one-shot ledger event). Added "stock_movement" to the OfflineEntityType union in types/offline.types.ts. 5 new tests in stockLocalRepository.test.ts (fails closed x3, queues correctly, lists only stock_movement records amongst mixed entity types).
Implementation (3 - receipt import): Recreated mbam-web/src/types/receiptImport.ts verbatim from git history (`git show 0fa8dd5:...`, same 2026-06-18 deletion) with the same kind of header note. Added new mbam-web/src/services/receiptImport/receiptImportLocalRepository.ts: `queueReceiptImportDraft` validates file size (<=10MB) and MIME type (jpeg/png/webp only) BEFORE checking the offline grant/`receipt_import.create` permission (also fail-closed today), queues the full payload (image metadata + base64 bytes) via the outbox under a new "receipt_import" entityType, but returns only the lightweight ReceiptImageDraft metadata to the caller -- imageBase64 never leaks back out of queue or list calls. `listQueuedReceiptImportDrafts` mirrors the stock listing pattern. 6 new tests in receiptImportLocalRepository.test.ts.
Docs updated: Added a "Status (2026-07-05)" note to both docs/future-stock-management.md and docs/future-receipt-import.md explaining the offline-layer slice now exists but no backend module/permission/UI does; added a parenthetical on each doc's "Prepared frontend contract" section noting the type file was deleted as dead code 2026-06-18 then recreated once a real consumer existed. Added services/stock/ and services/receiptImport/ rows to REPOSITORY_MAP.md's frontend services table. Added both new repository files to the "Active modules" list in mbam-web/src/services/localSync/README.md.
