Change: Made Reports precise/audit-grade: arbitrary custom date-range timeframes and a role-gated raw transaction/line-item detail report, both usable and printable.
Implementation (backend, mbam-api/src/modules/reports/): Added `custom` to the timeframe enum end-to-end. `ReportQuery` gained optional `start_date`/`end_date` (inclusive `YYYY-MM-DD`); `parse_custom_range` validates format, ordering, and a 731-day cap; `build_window` now takes an optional `(NaiveDate, NaiveDate)` custom range and picks bucket granularity by span (hour/day/month) instead of a fixed preset bucket. Added `GET /api/v1/reports/transactions` (`reports::service::transaction_detail`) returning a flat, printable one-row-per-transaction-line report (customer, payment method, status, recorded-by, per-line product/sku/qty/price) capped at 2000 rows with a `truncated` flag, including every transaction status (not just non-refunded) since this is meant as an audit record. Restricted to Master Owner + Business Admin via `require_baseline_role`, on top of the existing `report.view` scope check reused from the aggregate reports (`business_ids_for_permission`/`business_unit_ids_for_permission`/cashier `recorded_by_user_id` restriction, though cashier can never reach this route). Explicit `business_id`/`business_unit_id` filters are validated against the caller's grants (extracted into a new `validate_requested_business_scope` shared with the existing per-dimension `validate_requested_scope`); denials and successful views are both audit-logged (`authorization.report.denied` / `report.detail.viewed`) via the existing audit module.
Implementation (frontend, mbam-web/src/): `ReportTimeframe` gained `"custom"`; `ReportFilters` gained `startDate`/`endDate`; new `loadReportTransactionDetail()` in reportService.ts. `TimeframeControl.tsx` gained a 5th "Custom" button that reveals start/end `<input type="date">` fields (`CustomRange` type, `onCustomRangeChange` prop); wired into both ReportsPage.tsx and EntityReportDetailPage.tsx, each guarding their fetch effects on a valid (complete, non-inverted) range and showing a "pick a range" message otherwise. ReportsPage.tsx gained a role-gated (master_owner/business_admin only, matching the backend gate) Summary/Detail toggle; Detail mode renders new `pages/reports/ReportDetailTable.tsx`, a printable flattened table of every transaction line in scope/timeframe, with its own Print button, truncation warning, and print CSS (page-break-inside avoid, overflow visible, compact font on print) in new ReportDetailTable.css. Added `printReport`/custom-range/detail-toggle/detail-table i18n keys (en/fr) to reportsPageResources.ts and roleDashboardResources.ts.
Requested behavior: user found Reports "vague" and wanted (1) variable/custom timeframes and (2) printed raw-data tables showing fine-grained detail usable "as proof," with the explicit requirement that changes respect role permissions and that higher-up roles can choose how detailed a report they want.
