Implementation: New `mbam-api/src/dev_demo_data.rs`. `seed_demo_business(db)` runs once at startup (gated `config.app_env == "development"`, same as the existing seed): idempotent upserts of a master owner, business admin, 3 shop managers, and 3 cashiers (all `*.demo@mbam.local`) across a 3-shop "Mbam Demo Retail Group" business with 12 products (Groceries/Electronics, the only two categories with i18n coverage), then deletes and rebuilds a 20-day historical transaction backfill (tagged `idempotency_key like 'demo-seed-backfill-%'`, rebuilt relative to "now" on every restart so it never goes stale). `spawn_demo_traffic_worker(db)` is a `tokio::spawn` background loop (mirroring the existing `keycloak_sync::service::spawn_worker` pattern) that inserts one new realistic transaction every 75 seconds for the life of the server, tagged `demo-live-<uuid>` so these rows are never deleted and accumulate across restarts. Both paths share a deterministic field generator (`demo_transaction_fields`) that varies customer name, payment method, line items/quantities, and occasional pending/refunded status via modulo arithmetic on a sequence counter — no `rand` dependency, fully reproducible. Wired into `main.rs`: `mod dev_demo_data;`, `seed_demo_business` called right after the existing `dev_seed::seed_test_accounts` inside the same `if config.app_env == "development"` block (non-fatal `tracing::warn!` on error), and `spawn_demo_traffic_worker` called after `AppState::new`, gated the same way.
