2026-07-03T14:57:35Z UTC
Change: Added 30-second auto-refresh polling to the four role dashboards (master/business/shop/cashier), per explicit user request after they confirmed the demo-data live-traffic worker was actually inserting rows (visible in the `cargo run` logs) but an already-open dashboard tab never showed the new transactions.
Root cause: `BaselineDashboard` (`BaselineDashboards.tsx`) only fetched `loadDashboardSummary()`/`listRecentCloudTransactions()` once, inside a `useEffect` with no interval and no re-fetch trigger. This was correct behavior for a normal user session before the live-traffic worker existed, but once `dev_demo_data.rs` started inserting a new transaction every 75 seconds in the background (previous change), nothing in the frontend ever asked for the new data — the dashboard was only ever as fresh as the moment the tab was opened.
Implementation: Added a `DASHBOARD_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000` constant and refactored the load effect into a reusable `fetchDashboardData(isInitialLoad)` closure. The initial call still sets `state` to `"loading"` (full-page spinner) and clears data to `null`/`[]` on failure, matching prior behavior exactly. A `window.setInterval` then calls the same fetch every 30s with `isInitialLoad = false`: on success it swaps in the new `summary`/`transactions` silently (no loading spinner, no flicker); on failure it logs via the existing `logger.debug` pattern and deliberately keeps showing the last good data instead of replacing it with the error state, so a single transient network blip doesn't blank out an otherwise-working dashboard. The interval is cleared in the effect's cleanup function alongside the existing `ignore` flag, so it stops on unmount/route change and never fires after a dependency change re-runs the effect.
Files changed: `mbam-web/src/pages/dashboard/BaselineDashboards.tsx`.
Verification: `npx tsc --noEmit` clean; `npm run lint` clean (`--max-warnings 0`); `npm test` passed (21 files / 57 tests, unchanged — confirmed no existing test renders `BaselineDashboards`/any of its four exported dashboard components, so nothing exercises the new interval in the test suite); `npx vite build --mode production --outDir <temp dir>` succeeded.
Checks not run: No live browser verification (no local Docker/Keycloak stack in this sandbox) — recommend the user open a demo-account dashboard and watch a metric update within one or two 30s polls without manually reloading.
Remaining risks: 30s was chosen as a reasonable middle ground against the live-traffic worker's 75s insert interval (catches each new transaction within 1-3 polls) without being aggressive enough to matter for a local dev-only feature; adjust `DASHBOARD_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` if that cadence feels off. Polling continues even when the browser tab is backgrounded/hidden (no `document.visibilitychange` gating) — acceptable for a local dev tool hitting `localhost`, but would be worth adding before this pattern is reused anywhere user-facing or hitting a shared/production API, to avoid needless load from many idle background tabs.

