Backend dead-code audit: No Rust toolchain in this sandbox, so no `cargo build`/`clippy` unused-code warnings available. Ran a grep-based pass instead -- for every `pub fn`/`pub struct`/`pub enum` in `mbam-api/src`, counted total occurrences of its name across the whole tree; zero results came back as single-occurrence (i.e., no public item was found completely unreferenced). Also confirmed every `.rs` file is declared by a `mod` statement somewhere (no orphaned/uncompiled files). Concluded the backend has no obvious dead code at the public-item level; a full `cargo build`/`cargo clippy --all-targets` locally would still be the authoritative check for unused private items, which grep can't reliably isolate.
